If one of the following provisions of the Maryland Uniform Commercial Code specifies the applicable law, that provision governs and a contrary agreement is effective only to the extent permitted by the law (including the conflict of laws rules) so specified:
Section 2-402;
Sections 2A-105 and 2A-106;
Section 4-102;
Section 4A-507;
Section 5-116;
Section 6-103;
Section 8-110; or
Sections 9-301 through 9-307.
